"{\"uid\": \"theatlantic.com-health-archive-2024-08-olympic-marathon-invention-679432\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"A 19th-century philologist turned a Greek legend into a sport.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 62, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 36, \"end\": 41, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"score\": 0.9999547118801191, \"rank\": 4.528979804894772e-05, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A 19th-century philologist\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 26}, {\"ngram\": \"a sport\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 61}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris Olympics'picturesque marathon coursewill take runners past many of the city's highlights-the Palace of Versailles, the Louvre's glass pyramid, the Eiffel Tower.\", \"from\": 66, \"to\": 236, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 70, \"end\": 75, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999645297, \"rank\": 3.5409356969749973e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"runners\", \"from\": 122, \"to\": 129}, {\"ngram\": \"the city's highlights\", \"from\": 143, \"to\": 164}, {\"ngram\": \"the Palace\", \"from\": 165, \"to\": 175}, {\"ngram\": \"Versailles\", \"from\": 179, \"to\": 189}, {\"ngram\": \"the Louvre's glass pyramid\", \"from\": 191, \"to\": 217}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 219, \"to\": 235}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But it will miss, by miles, a plain one-block street in the 13th arrondissement namedRue Michel-Br\\u00e9al.\", \"from\": 237, \"to\": 339, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"miles\", \"from\": 258, \"to\": 263}, {\"ngram\": \"a plain one-block street\", \"from\": 265, \"to\": 289}, {\"ngram\": \"the 13th\", \"from\": 293, \"to\": 301}, {\"ngram\": \"arrondissement namedRue Michel-Br\\u00e9al\", \"from\": 302, \"to\": 338}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That's a shame, given that Michel Br\\u00e9al is the reason anyone ever ran a marathon on purpose.\", \"from\": 340, \"to\": 432, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 367, \"end\": 379, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michel_Br\\u00e9al\", \"score\": 0.9999991054173187, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Michel Br\\u00e9al\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michel_Br\\u00e9al\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michel_Br\\u00e9al\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a shame\", \"from\": 347, \"to\": 354}, {\"ngram\": \"the reason\", \"from\": 383, \"to\": 393}, {\"ngram\": \"anyone\", \"from\": 394, \"to\": 400}, {\"ngram\": \"a marathon\", \"from\": 410, \"to\": 420}, {\"ngram\": \"purpose\", \"from\": 424, \"to\": 431}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Without a Br\\u00e9al brainstorm and a letter he wrote in 1894, the number of people who run marathons each year would be zero instead ofmore than 1 million.\", \"from\": 436, \"to\": 587, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a Br\\u00e9al brainstorm\", \"from\": 444, \"to\": 462}, {\"ngram\": \"a letter\", \"from\": 467, \"to\": 475}, {\"ngram\": \"the number\", \"from\": 494, \"to\": 504}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 508, \"to\": 514}, {\"ngram\": \"marathons\", \"from\": 523, \"to\": 532}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A lot of Saturday mornings would be freed up for something other thanlong runs.Bibswould be reserved for babies.\", \"from\": 588, \"to\": 700, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A lot\", \"from\": 588, \"to\": 593}, {\"ngram\": \"Saturday mornings\", \"from\": 597, \"to\": 614}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 637, \"to\": 646}, {\"ngram\": \"other thanlong runs\", \"from\": 647, \"to\": 666}, {\"ngram\": \"babies\", \"from\": 693, \"to\": 699}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So many nippleswould go unchafed.\", \"from\": 701, \"to\": 734, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"To the extent that Br\\u00e9al is remembered today, it's as a 19th-centuryscholar of languagesandmythology, a leader ofFrench education reform, and the man who coined the wordsemantics.\", \"from\": 738, \"to\": 917, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the extent\", \"from\": 741, \"to\": 751}, {\"ngram\": \"Br\\u00e9al\", \"from\": 757, \"to\": 762}, {\"ngram\": \"a 19th-centuryscholar\", \"from\": 792, \"to\": 813}, {\"ngram\": \"languagesandmythology\", \"from\": 817, \"to\": 838}, {\"ngram\": \"a leader ofFrench education reform\", \"from\": 840, \"to\": 874}, {\"ngram\": \"the man\", \"from\": 880, \"to\": 887}, {\"ngram\": \"the wordsemantics\", \"from\": 899, \"to\": 916}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But he was also an acquaintance of a young man named Pierre du Coubertin, the secretary general of the Union of French Sports Associations, who was active in education reform and, by the early 1890s, planning a revival of the ancient-Greek Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 918, \"to\": 1172, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an acquaintance\", \"from\": 934, \"to\": 949}, {\"ngram\": \"a young man\", \"from\": 953, \"to\": 964}, {\"ngram\": \"Pierre\", \"from\": 971, \"to\": 977}, {\"ngram\": \"du Coubertin\", \"from\": 978, \"to\": 990}, {\"ngram\": \"the secretary general\", \"from\": 992, \"to\": 1013}, {\"ngram\": \"the Union\", \"from\": 1017, \"to\": 1026}, {\"ngram\": \"French Sports Associations\", \"from\": 1030, \"to\": 1056}, {\"ngram\": \"education reform\", \"from\": 1076, \"to\": 1092}, {\"ngram\": \"a revival\", \"from\": 1127, \"to\": 1136}, {\"ngram\": \"the ancient-Greek Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1140, \"to\": 1171}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Br\\u00e9al, three decades Coubertin's senior, was a leading intellectual of the day, a commander of the French Legion of Honor: the sort of person needed to bring gravitas to the idea of an international festival of athletics.\", \"from\": 1176, \"to\": 1397, \"entities\": [], \"nou