\", \"from\": 4293, \"to\": 4316}, {\"ngram\": \"the exhausted runners\", \"from\": 4326, \"to\": 4347}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And when a Greek water carrier namedSpyridon Louiswas first to enter the stadium, a new national hero was born.\", \"from\": 4349, \"to\": 4460, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4360, \"end\": 4365, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"score\": 0.9999547118801191, \"rank\": 4.528979804894772e-05, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"namedSpyridon\", \"from\": 4380, \"to\": 4393}, {\"ngram\": \"the stadium\", \"from\": 4418, \"to\": 4429}, {\"ngram\": \"a new national hero\", \"from\": 4431, \"to\": 4450}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For his victory, Louis received, as promised, asilver cupdonated by Michel Br\\u00e9al.\", \"from\": 4461, \"to\": 4542, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4529, \"end\": 4541, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michel_Br\\u00e9al\", \"score\": 0.9999991054173187, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Michel Br\\u00e9al\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michel_Br\\u00e9al\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michel_Br\\u00e9al\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his victory\", \"from\": 4465, \"to\": 4476}, {\"ngram\": \"Louis\", \"from\": 4478, \"to\": 4483}, {\"ngram\": \"asilver\", \"from\": 4507, \"to\": 4514}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It now sitsin the Acropolis Museum.\", \"from\": 4543, \"to\": 4578, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4561, \"end\": 4577, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Acropolis_Museum\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Acropolis Museum\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q33506\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Acropolis_Museum\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Acropolis_Museum\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The marathon race was an immediate success, spawning emulators around the world and transforming long-distance running into a sport.\", \"from\": 4582, \"to\": 4714, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The marathon race\", \"from\": 4582, \"to\": 4599}, {\"ngram\": \"an immediate success\", \"from\": 4604, \"to\": 4624}, {\"ngram\": \"emulators\", \"from\": 4635, \"to\": 4644}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 4652, \"to\": 4661}, {\"ngram\": \"long-distance\", \"from\": 4679, \"to\": 4692}, {\"ngram\": \"a sport\", \"from\": 4706, \"to\": 4713}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A 1908 Olympics report described an \\\"epidemic of 'Marathon Races' which attacked the civilised world from Madison Square Gardens to the Valley of the Nile.\\\"\", \"from\": 4715, \"to\": 4871, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A 1908 Olympics report\", \"from\": 4715, \"to\": 4737}, {\"ngram\": \"an \\\"epidemic\", \"from\": 4748, \"to\": 4760}, {\"ngram\": \"'Marathon Races\", \"from\": 4764, \"to\": 4779}, {\"ngram\": \"the civilised world\", \"from\": 4796, \"to\": 4815}, {\"ngram\": \"Madison Square Gardens\", \"from\": 4821, \"to\": 4843}, {\"ngram\": \"the Valley\", \"from\": 4847, \"to\": 4857}, {\"ngram\": \"the Nile\", \"from\": 4861, \"to\": 4869}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That rash of imitators also canonized Br\\u00e9al's version of the ancient run.\", \"from\": 4875, \"to\": 4948, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"That rash\", \"from\": 4875, \"to\": 4884}, {\"ngram\": \"imitators\", \"from\": 4888, \"to\": 4897}, {\"ngram\": \"Br\\u00e9al's version\", \"from\": 4913, \"to\": 4928}, {\"ngram\": \"the ancient run\", \"from\": 4932, \"to\": 4947}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is no contemporary evidence that a man named Pheidippides even did run from Marathon to Athens.\", \"from\": 4949, \"to\": 5050, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5000, \"end\": 5012, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pheidippides\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pheidippides\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q1908